                        <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This item is a typescript copy of the original letter which was sent on February 6, 1919 to G.E. Nelson, president of the Old Salem League. The letter was read during a celebration of Lincoln&#039;s birthday held by the Old Salem League on February 12, 1919, and it was also published in the <emph render="italic">Illinois State Register</emph> on February 13, 1919. In the letter, Henry B. Rankin describes Lincoln&#039;s life during his time in New Salem, and he criticizes writers and a sculptor who he believes had defamed the character of Lincoln in their works. Rankin studied law under Lincoln and William Herndon from 1856-1861, and he wrote articles and pamphlets about Lincoln including <emph render="italic">Personal Recollections of Abraham Lincoln</emph>, and <emph render="italic">Intimate Character Sketches of Abraham Lincoln</emph>.</p>
                                 <p>The item was previously cataloged in the Lincoln Room with the call number Q.MS 973.7 L63 GR1671.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


